Welcome to This Majestic Flying Day

On June 6, 1944, the Allies landed on the beaches of Normandy during a short period of favorable weather, changing the process of World War II. 77 years later, the Imperial War Museum Duxford commemorated the soldiers, pilots and sailors who joined the landing operation against all emeries with a "D-Day anniversary air show" which is the same as the world have been fighting for its own D-Day since the start of the COVID-19 pandemic.

On this site, you will find three highlights of the day, a number of magnificent images of the ‘heavy iron’ warbirds, information about participating in the flying day, information about the Imperial War Museum, and profiles of the photographer.
